hacks that I had to make: Build a multiple-page application using React Navigation.

## Answers to the lab questions:
    answer #a 
    The Stack Navigator is used to implement separate pages of an application in React Native.

    answer #b
    The Route in React Navigation is analogous to a URL/URI on the Web.

    answer #c
    No, we cannot just say `navigation.navigate('Details')` because it would execute the navigation 
    immediately when the component is rendered, rather than waiting for the button press event.

    answer #d
    The hard-coded movie list is displayed on the homepage using a FlatList component that maps over 
    the reviews array and renders each movie title as a TouchableOpacity, allowing users to tap on a 
    title to navigate to the details screen.

    answer #e
    The details screen shows the selected movie's detail by accessing the parameters passed from the 
    previous screen. It retrieves these details from route.params, which contains the information about 
    the chosen movie.
